{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1770128378,"nonce":"LIhxhtbKxZAchb392xDZ/alSoKU=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87k-mlj","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/136#issuecomment-3841616227"},"message":"## Investigation Complete ✅\n\n**Question**: Can Conductor be used with all agentic frameworks?\n\n**Answer**: ❌ **No** - Conductor is Gemini CLI-specific and incompatible with our multi-agent architecture.\n\n---\n\n### Key Findings\n\n#### Incompatibilities\n\n1. **Framework Lock-in**: Conductor is a Gemini CLI extension that uses slash commands (`/conductor:setup`, `/conductor:implement`, etc.). It cannot be used by:\n   - ❌ GitHub Copilot CLI\n   - ❌ Antigravity\n   - ❌ Claude CLI\n   - ❌ Shell scripts or automation\n\n2. **Feature Overlap**: ~70% of Conductor functionality already exists in our `.agent/` structure:\n   - Context management: `.agent/AI_RULES.md`, `knowledge/`, `workflows/`\n   - Track planning: GitHub Issues + `.agent/work-plans/`\n   - Workflow definitions: `.agent/workflows/` + `CLI_COMMANDS.md`\n   - Tech stack docs: `.agent/knowledge/ros2_*.md`\n\n3. **Directory Structure Conflict**: \n   - Conductor creates `conductor/` at project root\n   - We have `.agent/` serving the same purpose\n   - Would create parallel/redundant structures\n\n4. **High Migration Cost**: \n   - Would need to merge 78+ `.agent/*.md` files into Conductor structure\n   - Require Gemini CLI installation for all developers\n   - Abandon multi-agent compatibility\n   - **Estimated effort**: 20-30 hours\n\n---\n\n### What We Can Learn From Conductor\n\nWhile we shouldn't adopt Conductor wholesale, we can **borrow valuable patterns**:\n\n#### ✅ Pattern 1: Structured Track Planning\nImprove GitHub issue templates with Conductor-style structure:\n```markdown\n## Spec\n- User story\n- Acceptance criteria  \n- Out of scope\n\n## Plan\n### Phase 1: Foundation\n- [ ] Task 1\n  - [ ] Subtask 1a\n  - [ ] Subtask 1b\n```\n\n#### ✅ Pattern 2: Plan-Before-Code Enforcement\nAdd to `.agent/AI_RULES.md`:\n\u003e For features/bugs: Create spec → Create plan → Get approval → THEN code\n\n#### ✅ Pattern 3: Phase Verification Checkpoints\nAfter each major phase: Run tests → User verification → Get approval → Continue\n\n#### ✅ Pattern 4: Git-Aware Feature Revert\nCreate `.agent/scripts/revert_feature.sh`:\n```bash\n# Revert all commits for a GitHub issue/feature\n./revert_feature.sh --issue 137\n```\n\n---\n\n### Recommendation\n\n**Primary Path**: ✅ **Keep `.agent/` structure, borrow Conductor patterns**\n\n**Action Items**:\n1. Create Conductor-inspired GitHub issue template (`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature_track.md`)\n2. Add \"Plan Before Code\" rule to `.agent/AI_RULES.md`\n3. Implement phase verification checkpoints in workflows\n4. Create git-aware feature revert script\n\n**DO NOT**:\n- ❌ Install Conductor plugin\n- ❌ Migrate to `conductor/` directory structure  \n- ❌ Abandon multi-agent compatibility\n\n---\n\n### Conclusion\n\nConductor's philosophy of \"context as code\" aligns well with our `.agent/` approach, but the technical implementation is incompatible with our multi-framework requirements. We gain more value by evolving our existing structure with Conductor-inspired patterns than by adopting the plugin.\n\n**Closing this issue as**: Won't implement - incompatible with multi-agent architecture\n\n---\n**🤖 Analysis By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1770129301,"nonce":"ogMczrnT8EF5VlRSBzyYAfxoUXk=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87n0H_2zwAAAAU9EMFZ"},"status":2}]}